POLOKWANE – 19 Families from Seshego Zone 2 were given food parcels on Wednesday (June 29) as part of a donation by the Nazia Carrim Attorneys law firm. You might also want to read: Refinery give back to needy learners in Seshego The parcels were received by the Christian Ark 4 Alms Foundation (Caaf), who pride themselves on being a small charity organisation that makes a great impact. The law firm’s visit and donation was made in good faith and director, Nazia Carrim said they heard about the foundation through a coworker. “We are thankful to be in a position where we can bless others, even if it is just a meal. We learnt about the families who rely on this foundation and decided to visit the area and share with the community. This is the second organization we have managed to assist and we intend to make it a regular occurrence,” she said. They also shared a meal with the 19 beneficiaries and their families. Caaf president Kefilwe Tjale told BONUS that the foundation is grateful for the donation and blessed that they were able to share the afternoon together. Read the full story in next week’s BONUS Review. 